---
/**
 * RexSessionDemo — an app-realistic phone mockup that walks ONE real job
 * (a kitchen-sink P-trap drain leak) through all five Rex session stages.
 * Built to match the homepage Rex demo (PhoneMockup.astro): same phone frame,
 * status bar, "Rex" header, chat bubbles, and the animated Rex compass as
 * Rex's avatar / thinking indicator.
 */
import LottiePlayer from "./react/LottiePlayer.tsx";
import Icon from "./Icon.astro";

const stages = [
  "Context Capture",
  "Problem Identification",
  "Diagnosis",
  "Step-by-Step Guidance",
  "Completion",
];
---

<div class="relative mx-auto w-[300px] sm:w-[320px]">
  <!-- glow -->
  <div
    class="absolute -inset-6 -z-10 rounded-[3rem] bg-blue/20 blur-3xl"
    aria-hidden="true"
  >
  </div>

  <div
    class="overflow-hidden rounded-[2.5rem] border-[10px] border-navy-900 bg-white shadow-[var(--shadow-lift)]"
  >
    <!-- status bar -->
    <div class="flex items-center justify-between bg-navy px-5 py-3 text-white">
      <span class="text-xs font-semibold">9:41</span>
      <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 text-xs font-bold">
        <span class="h-1.5 w-1.5 rounded-full bg-success"></span> Rex
      </span>
    </div>

    <!-- app header -->
    <div class="flex items-center gap-2.5 border-b border-navy/5 bg-white px-4 py-2.5">
      <span class="grid h-8 w-8 place-items-center rounded-full bg-navy text-blue">
        <Icon name="compass" size={18} />
      </span>
      <div class="leading-tight">
        <p class="text-sm font-extrabold text-navy">Rex</p>
        <p class="text-[0.65rem] text-body">Kitchen-sink drain leak</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-3 bg-tint px-3.5 py-4">
      <!-- STAGE 1 — Context Capture -->
      <div class="flex items-center justify-center">
        <span class="rounded-full bg-navy/5 px-2.5 py-1 text-[0.6rem] font-bold uppercase tracking-wide text-navy/60"
          >Stage 1 · {stages[0]}</span
        >
      </div>

      <!-- rex: context questions -->
      <div class="flex items-end gap-1.5">
        <span class="grid h-7 w-7 shrink-0 place-items-center rounded-full bg-navy text-blue">
          <Icon name="compass" size={15} />
        </span>
        <div class="mr-auto max-w-[85%] rounded-2xl rounded-bl-sm bg-white px-3.5 py-2.5 shadow-sm">
          <p class="text-sm leading-snug text-navy">
            Quick context so I get this right: residential, light commercial, or
            industrial? What state? Roughly how old is the system? And on
            plumbing — municipal or well, pipe material, and is this potable,
            drain-waste-vent, or gas?
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- worker: answer -->
      <div class="ml-auto max-w-[82%] rounded-2xl rounded-br-sm bg-navy px-3.5 py-2.5 text-white">
        <p class="text-sm leading-snug">
          Residential, Ohio, ~30 years old. Municipal, PVC, kitchen sink DWV.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- STAGE 2 — Problem Identification -->
      <div class="flex items-center justify-center pt-1">
        <span class="rounded-full bg-navy/5 px-2.5 py-1 text-[0.6rem] font-bold uppercase tracking-wide text-navy/60"
          >Stage 2 · {stages[1]}</span
        >
      </div>

      <!-- worker: photo + voice note -->
      <div class="ml-auto max-w-[82%] rounded-2xl rounded-br-sm bg-navy px-2.5 pb-2.5 pt-2.5 text-white">
        <div class="mb-2 overflow-hidden rounded-xl">
          <div class="flex aspect-[4/3] flex-col items-center justify-center gap-1 bg-gradient-to-br from-navy-900 to-blue/40 text-white/70">
            <Icon name="camera" size={22} />
            <span class="text-[0.6rem] font-semibold">Photo · under-sink leak</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="flex items-center gap-1.5 text-sm leading-snug">
          <Icon name="mic" size={13} /> Water pooling under the kitchen sink — looks
          like it's from the trap.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- rex: assessment -->
      <div class="flex items-end gap-1.5">
        <span class="grid h-7 w-7 shrink-0 place-items-center rounded-full bg-navy text-blue">
          <Icon name="compass" size={15} />
        </span>
        <div class="mr-auto max-w-[85%] rounded-2xl rounded-bl-sm bg-white px-3.5 py-2.5 shadow-sm">
          <p class="text-sm leading-snug text-navy">
            From the photo, the leak is at the slip-joint between the P-trap and
            the trap arm — staining and active moisture at that joint, not the
            tailpiece above. That's a slow joint leak, not an overflow.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- STAGE 3 — Diagnosis -->
      <div class="flex items-center justify-center pt-1">
        <span class="rounded-full bg-navy/5 px-2.5 py-1 text-[0.6rem] font-bold uppercase tracking-wide text-navy/60"
          >Stage 3 · {stages[2]}</span
        >
      </div>

      <!-- rex thinking — animated compass -->
      <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
        <span class="grid h-7 w-7 shrink-0 place-items-center rounded-full bg-white shadow-sm">
          <LottiePlayer
            client:visible
            src="/assets/motion/Rex_Thinking_Loop.json"
            className="h-5 w-5"
            ariaLabel="Rex thinking"
          />
        </span>
        <span class="text-[0.7rem] font-semibold text-body">Rex is putting it together…</span>
      </div>

      <!-- structured diagnosis card -->
      <div class="mr-auto w-full max-w-[92%] rounded-2xl rounded-bl-sm bg-white px-3.5 py-3 shadow-sm">
        <p class="mb-2 text-[0.6rem] font-bold uppercase tracking-wide text-blue">
          Diagnosis
        </p>
        <dl class="space-y-1.5 text-[0.78rem] leading-snug">
          <div>
            <dt class="inline font-bold text-navy">Diagnosis: </dt>
            <dd class="inline text-body">Failed slip-joint seal at the P-trap / trap-arm connection.</dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt class="inline font-bold text-navy">Issue: </dt>
            <dd class="inline text-body">The slip washer has lost its seal — it weeps under normal flow.</dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt class="inline font-bold text-navy">Cause: </dt>
            <dd class="inline text-body">Aged/compressed or over-tightened slip washer. Not a pipe failure.</dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt class="inline font-bold text-navy">Solution: </dt>
            <dd class="inline text-body">
              Replace the slip washer, re-seat hand-tight plus a quarter turn.
              Alternative: replace the trap assembly if it's brittle or
              discolored.
            </dd>
          </div>
        </dl>
        <div class="mt-2 flex items-center gap-1.5 rounded-lg bg-tint px-2 py-1.5 text-[0.7rem] font-semibold text-blue">
          <Icon name="doc" size={14} /> IPC 2021 §1002 · trap seal &amp; trap-arm
        </div>
        <p class="mt-2 text-[0.68rem] leading-snug text-body/80">
          Verify current adoption in your jurisdiction — local amendments may
          apply.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- rex: confirm before moving on -->
      <div class="flex items-end gap-1.5">
        <span class="grid h-7 w-7 shrink-0 place-items-center rounded-full bg-navy text-blue">
          <Icon name="compass" size={15} />
        </span>
        <div class="mr-auto max-w-[85%] rounded-2xl rounded-bl-sm bg-white px-3.5 py-2.5 shadow-sm">
          <p class="text-sm leading-snug text-navy">
            Want me to walk you through the fix, step by step?
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- STAGE 4 — Step-by-Step Guidance -->
      <div class="flex items-center justify-center pt-1">
        <span class="rounded-full bg-navy/5 px-2.5 py-1 text-[0.6rem] font-bold uppercase tracking-wide text-navy/60"
          >Stage 4 · {stages[3]}</span
        >
      </div>

      <!-- rex: step 1 -->
      <div class="flex items-end gap-1.5">
        <span class="grid h-7 w-7 shrink-0 place-items-center rounded-full bg-navy text-blue">
          <Icon name="compass" size={15} />
        </span>
        <div class="mr-auto max-w-[85%] rounded-2xl rounded-bl-sm bg-white px-3.5 py-2.5 shadow-sm">
          <p class="text-sm leading-snug text-navy">
            Step 1: clear the cabinet, pan under the trap, disconnect the slip
            nuts. Send me a photo of the removed washer.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- worker: removed-washer photo -->
      <div class="ml-auto max-w-[82%] rounded-2xl rounded-br-sm bg-navy px-2.5 pb-1 pt-2.5 text-white">
        <div class="overflow-hidden rounded-xl">
          <div class="flex aspect-[4/3] flex-col items-center justify-center gap-1 bg-gradient-to-br from-navy-900 to-blue/40 text-white/70">
            <Icon name="camera" size={22} />
            <span class="text-[0.6rem] font-semibold">Photo · removed washer</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- rex: assess + next step -->
      <div class="flex items-end gap-1.5">
        <span class="grid h-7 w-7 shrink-0 place-items-center rounded-full bg-navy text-blue">
          <Icon name="compass" size={15} />
        </span>
        <div class="mr-auto max-w-[85%] rounded-2xl rounded-bl-sm bg-white px-3.5 py-2.5 shadow-sm">
          <p class="text-sm leading-snug text-navy">
            That washer's compressed and grooved — there's your leak. Step 2:
            seat the new washer, hand-tight plus a quarter turn. No
            over-torquing.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- STAGE 5 — Completion -->
      <div class="flex items-center justify-center pt-1">
        <span class="rounded-full bg-navy/5 px-2.5 py-1 text-[0.6rem] font-bold uppercase tracking-wide text-navy/60"
          >Stage 5 · {stages[4]}</span
        >
      </div>

      <!-- rex: final test -->
      <div class="flex items-end gap-1.5">
        <span class="grid h-7 w-7 shrink-0 place-items-center rounded-full bg-navy text-blue">
          <Icon name="compass" size={15} />
        </span>
        <div class="mr-auto max-w-[85%] rounded-2xl rounded-bl-sm bg-white px-3.5 py-2.5 shadow-sm">
          <p class="text-sm leading-snug text-navy">
            Run the tap 30 seconds, fill and release the basin for a full-load
            test, dry the joint and check for weep. Confirm the trap arm still
            slopes 1/4 inch per foot. Dry under load? You're done.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- job-close action -->
      <div class="mr-auto ml-9 w-[85%] rounded-xl border border-blue/20 bg-white px-3.5 py-3 shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-navy">
          <span class="grid h-7 w-7 place-items-center rounded-lg bg-success/15 text-success">
            <Icon name="check" size={16} />
          </span>
          <p class="text-sm font-extrabold">Job closed</p>
        </div>
        <button
          type="button"
          class="mt-2.5 flex w-full items-center justify-center gap-1.5 rounded-lg bg-navy px-3 py-2 text-[0.78rem] font-bold text-white"
        >
          <Icon name="doc" size={14} /> Generate report &amp; quote
        </button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
